# Where Does AI Fit In?

#### In this course, AI is a helper, not a replacement for students’ thinking. Students stay in control of the design and coding process, while AI serves as a creative partner that can suggest, outline, or refine ideas.

## How Students Use AI

 
 


<div style="display: flex; gap: 20px; justify-content: space-between;flex-wrap: wrap;">
  
  <!-- Block 1 -->
  <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 250px; background-color: #B7E0E5; padding: 20px; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
    <div style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 10px;text-align: center;">💡</div>
    <h3 style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; text-align: center;"><b>As a brainstorming tool:</b></h3>
    <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 14pt; line-height: 1.5;">
      AI can suggest starting points (like a layout or function idea) that students then adapt and improve.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Block 2 -->
  <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 250px; background-color: #B7E0E5; padding: 20px; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
    <div style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 10px;text-align: center;">👩‍🏫</div>
    <h3 style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; text-align: center;"><b>As a tutor-on-demand:</b></h3>
    <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 14pt; line-height: 1.5;">
      AI can explain concepts step by step and offer hints instead of solutions.
    </p>
  </div>
 </div>
 <div style="clear:both;"></div>
<br>
  
  <div style="display: flex; gap: 20px; justify-content: space-between;flex-wrap: wrap;">
 
  <!-- Block 3 -->
  <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 250px; background-color: #B7E0E5; padding: 20px; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
    <div style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 10px;text-align: center;">🛠️</div>
    <h3 style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; text-align: center;"><b>As a collaborator in building:</b></h3>
    <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 14pt; line-height: 1.5;">
      AI helps write or refine HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, but students must review, edit, and debug.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Block 4 -->
